main event: A civilian observed an unidentified flying object from an apartment window in Chicago on March 25, 1966, for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
interesting points: The object was seen moving from northwest to southeast,The observer described the object as being extremely bright,The object faded away upon disappearance,No physical evidence was collected or photographs taken,The observer was a 25-year-old UPS driver with a good reliability rating being an Air Force veteran.
